args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor the Rage of Chronos event as well as\nYurius's adventurer story.

After Chronos's plot sees the young vampire Vania
brought into contact with {player_name},
she elects to stay at the Halidom, holding out hope
of one day saving her people. In the meantime...
Hee hee. I'm just so excited to finally\nhave a bloodkin of my very own!\nC'mon, let's go play!
Ouch... *ahem* Vania, I'd hoped that our\nprevious conversations made it clear that\nI can't dedicate my sole attention to you.
Whaaat? Sure you can.\nIt's decided. I decided it.
I've gotta get way, WAY stronger if I want\nto help my clan stuck sleeping back in the\nforest.
And they say there's nothing stronger than\nthe AMAZING bond a vampire shares with\nher bloodkin.
That's why we're besties now, you and me!
I...have any number of comments to make\nabout that, but I share your desire to be\ngood friends. You're a part of the Halidom.
When I do have time to spare, I'll gladly\nspend some of it with you. Okay, Vania?
Heh heh, yesss! I knew you had more than\nrocks rollin' around in that noggin of yours.
I'm gonna hold you to that promise, okay?\nWe are gonna paint the town RED!\nWith fun, I mean. Not blood.
(To be sure, I DID promise to spend time\nwith her. Still...)
Ha ha HAA! My sorcerer princess takes\nyour sellsword and...BLAMMO!\nSends it flying! Okay, it's your turn!
(She's so given to whimsy and caprice, I\nhave no idea what she expects of a play\npartner!)
Hellooo? No getting distracted! You said\nyou'd teach me Alberian chess, so focus!
Ah, you're right. Apologies.\nThen I'll move my woodland archer to—
Ugh, don't bother. This is no fun when your\nheart's obviously not in it. New game!
What? But you were the one who asked to\nlearn chess.
And now I'm telling you I'm over it! It's\ndoing zip to make me feel closer to you.
True; I suppose as a competitive game,\nit may not foster much of a connection\nbetween opponents.
Like I said, over it. Read to me instead.\nStart with the book on that shelf there!
I don't mind, but isn't that the same book\nyou dismissed as too complicated to follow\nthe other day?
Yesterday's algebra is today's arithmetic.\nNow, enough back-talk. Your mistress's\norders are absolute!
At it again with the spoiled little\nbloodsucker today, eh?
Seems like EVERY day, lately. She's glued\nto your side morning, noon, and night.
I'm impressed you can keep that up. I'd be\ntuning her out by now, no question! Even\nSarisse isn't THAT bad.
But she's known such loneliness.\nI can't bring myself to ignore her\npleas for company now.
You're a nicer guy than me, then.
Hmph. Did you two have some BUSINESS\nwith my bloodkin?
A new job just came in. You free to head\nout, {player_name}?
Yes, if needed, I'm happy to—
What?! No, absolutely not! He's busy with\nme today. EXTREMELY busy! Aren't you,\n{player_name}?
...It seems I'm unavailable. I'm sorry.\nCan the two of you manage alone?
Yeah, it ain't anything that big. But are ya\nsure you wanna hand her your leash like\nthis?
He's right, y'know. And Vania, what gives?\nWhy are you dragging the poor man around\nlike this?
So of COURSE we have to make our bond\nas strong as possible!
I'm sorry, your BOND? Gimme a break!
I don't think I like your tone, mister!
It's pretty rich hearing you say how\nclose you are after watching you\nbully the guy all week!
He's playing along because that's the kinda\nguy he is, but that's ALL it is. This isn't how\nyou connect with people!
He mighta gotten a little heated there,\nbut I'm with Luca on this one.
Listen, sister. Everybody's got their\nown needs. Their own life to live.
If you don't respect that and show a little\nconsideration, there ain't a lotta room\nthere for friendship 'n understanding.
Oh nooo... So everything I've done has\nbeen backfiring? We're still not connected?\nNot even a little?
Well, maybe a LITTLE... But no, not really.
Ugh, nooo! This is terrible. I can't very well\nbecome queen one day if I can't navigate\nthe whole interpersonal relationship thing.
What do I do, then? How do I connect with\nmy bloodkin and become a great mistress?
How about you start by asking him what\nHE wants to do every once in a while?
If he's struggling with something, help him\nout. If he's busy, give him some space.\nHe's got his own stuff to do, outside of you.
Hm. So patience is important, then. Okay.\nI'll try to work on practicing a little bit of\nrestraint.
I REALLY want to spend the day together...\nBut I can stay behind while he works,\nthis once.
Eyyy, she learns! You're more open-minded\nthan I expected, honestly.
Don't go getting the wrong idea! This is all\njust a part of being the best mistress to my\nbloodkin I can be.
Just you watch—I'm going to make our\nbond the strongest ever in record time!
